The paper proposes a new architecture called "PT-Spike" that uses precise single-spike temporal encoding, efficient supervised temporal learning, and fast asymmetric decoding to improve the energy efficiency and data processing capability of the time-based SNN. This work is closely related to the field of neural computing and is likely to be classified under cs.NE.
